<br>
In my opinion this completely invalidates any usefullness of the whole Lanys raid calendar...  The Swizeguy raid was posted the night of the emergency patch, even though our raid had been on the calendar for at least 1 if not 2 weeks prior.<br>
<br>
So what's the point of all this if somebody can come and ninja your spot?  /shrug  Yeah I know its all FFA and we're supposed to play nice which is why the raid calendar is here to begin with.<br>
<br>
Congrats to Swizeguy and all who were leading this ninja raid for demonstrating poor play style and a superb degree of inconsideration for the enjoyment of any others!<br>
<br>
Ignore me if you like, flame me if you want... /shrug  all flames are automatically redirected to /dev/null anyway <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Fabilaar Starcaller<BR>
Guild Leader<BR>
Chosen of Norrath<BR>
Humble mage of the 51st summoning<BR><BR>
Socializer  80% 
Explorer  80% 
Achiever  40% 
Killer  0% <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufalorsavageheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falor Savageheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/29/01 10:20:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naggy raid on dec 30 forced to be cancelled</span><hr size=1> Once again as stated 10 million times, the calendar is *not* a reservation system.  It is a posting of *intent*.  <br>
<br>
Expect emergency patches with a new expansion release.  Expect Naggy to go down right when the servers come back up.  There are many clerics needing their epics and having Naggy up for 1-2 days after patch does not help them with their epic.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  In my opinion this completely invalidates any usefullness of the whole Lanys raid calendar...  <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Read above.  The calendar is a good method to show intent.  That is what it was designed for.  No one &quot;ninja'd&quot; the raid.  If they did, you would have engaged it first, and their groups would have come and overpowered you for the kill.<br>
<br>
Flaming Swizeguy will not solve your problem.  Expect the above to happen with emergency patches. <p><center><a href="http://www.eqnow.com" target="_blank"><img src="http://filebox.vt.edu/users/anpainte/Falor_sig.jpg"></a><br>
