   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uboulvimethedras.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Boulvi Methedras</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/31/01 12:53:00 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.fortunecity.com/ludic/ezphoto.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> LOL miss the whole point altogether</span><hr size=1> My first post on this matter directly asked a specific two-part question. Never did it flame Swizeguy or anyone in that raid led by him. My questions were this: Are server patch raids commonplace and widely accepted? If so, then i cant wait til the next patch. If NOT, then what can be done about it. You peeps have completely missed the intent of the post. I commend Swizeguy on his efforts and achievement on killing Naggy. Now...this is where the hypocritical part of some of your posts hit home on me. Clerics need Ragefire and he only spawns when Naggy is dead so letting Naggy sit for 2-3 days isnt helping. Thats redundant. If Naggy is sitting there alive then its holding up Bards/Warriors/Paladins all the same. Im sorry but thats a piss poor excuse to go and kill Naggy. "Oh well i had to kill him so my cleric could get his epic" "Was your raid today?" Im sorry" "Sucks for you though"<br>
   All in all, you have answered my questions and added alot of no nonsense BS to boot. And i leave with one last question to consider. Had the terms been reciporacated ie. Their raid was Sunday and i held a server patch raid Saturday, how bad of a taste would have been left in their mouths? PS Naggy was NOT up on Tuesday. The raid before which was on a Saturday killed him...get your shit right before you post. Thank you and happy hunting. -Boulvi <p><a href="mailto:paladine26@aol.com"><img src="http://members.fortunecity.com/ludic/ezboulvi.jpg" alt="Click to Email Boulvi" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ueqmessup.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eqmessup</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/31/01 11:35:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LOL miss the whole point altogether</span><hr size=1> thats the way it always has been and always will be.  You expect a epic mob to sit their for 2, 3 , 4 days?  No way! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uryanilinholyknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryanilin Holyknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/3/02 3:21:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LOL miss the whole point altogether</span><hr size=1> Boulvi, perhaps I can lend you a bit of insight into how I used to approach Naggy and Vox when I was trying to get my books. In all honesty, planning a Naggy raid was a crap shoot at best, simply because, he might go down really late Thursday night, so someone plans a Friday kill the next week, which makes perfect sense.<br>
<br>
The problem comes in, when they patch on Tuesday, and announce the patch. If we go by the &quot;rules&quot; of the calendar (yes, I know it's not a reservation but even in the spirit of the thing) you only need 24 hours notice to post intent. Sounds to me like that happened here, and you were just on the wrong end of the stick. <br>
<br>
BUT... bear in mind, you too, can read about a patch, and post your intent to do Naggy the night he is up, even if you already have him posted in Friday, post again for Tuesday.<br>
<br>
I can't tell you how many times myself or my guildmates lost out on a dragon kill because he popped on the wrong day. /shrug It isn't easy to take, but it's the way it is. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showMessage?topicID=1851.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showMessage?topicID=1856.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.emailToFriend?topicID=1846.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.threadControl?topicID=1846.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1846.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1846.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub4.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="eqasylumgeneral">General<option value="eqasylumfrm33">Luclin Info<option value="eqasylumfrm25">Raid Discussions<option value="eqasylumthemerchantsunionbuyselltradeorannounceyourservicesforhire">The Merch